title: Republican Dan Newhouse Wins Re-election
description: One of 10 House Republicans who voted to impeach the former president for the Jan. 6, 2021, attack on the Capitol, Mr. Newhouse hung onto his seat.
dc:creator: Stephanie Lai

media:content.media:credit: Anna Rose Layden for The New York Times
media:content.media:description: Representative Dan Newhouse of Washington at a news conference in June. Mr. Newhouse secured his election to a fifth term in the House on Tuesday, surviving a challenge by Doug White, a Democrat.
